Today, Congress has the opportunity to expand, not the law, but rather, and instead, the number of Americans who can own a own home, or start their own business. #HMDAA

CFPB’s “double the data” rule is not just ineffective and costly, it also poses a threat to Americans’ privacy and data security. We must pass #HMDAA to give relief to Main Street banks and credit unions in Minnesota and across the country.

Due to the increased cost of compliance with the CFPB’s “double the data” rule – an estimated additional $326 million - many small banks in Minnesota are reconsidering their ability to continue to make mortgages and other covered loans. #HMDAA

Over the years the 1975 Home Mortgage Disclosure Act has expanded away from its original intent (to eliminate discriminatory lending). Dodd-Frank’s CFPB created a rule in 2015 to move it even further - requiring more than DOUBLE the data required to be reported. #HMDAA
Some laws have proven helpful to Americans who want a chance at the American Dream. Others have created obstacles by codifying government overreach. #HMDAA
COMING UP: I’m speaking on the House floor ahead of tonight's vote on my Home Mortgage Disclosure Adjustment Act. #HMDAA Stay tuned…

The time has come to put healthcare back in the hands of the American people by allowing them to choose their own doctors and coverage.
In MN, Blue Cross Blue Shield suffered major losses as a result of Obamacare’s failures, forcing them to drop individual plans.
As a result of these rising costs, many families have opted to go uninsured, rather than pay for these skyrocketing costs.
In MN alone, premiums have increased nearly 67% for 2017. Minnesotan families cannot, and should not, have to shoulder those costs.
